The HD 218566 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 218566 is a star with 0.76 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.85 times its radius. It is located 94.10 light years away from the solar system.

HD 218566 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 218566 system


HD 218566 b

HD 218566 b was discovered by the W. M. Keck Observatory observatory using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 0.69 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 218566 b is 63.6 times the mass of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 218566 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
